Figure \ref{C} shows the shapes of the effective potential and graviton zero mode in model B.
From Eqs.~(\ref{warp2}), (\ref{InitialCondition}), (\ref{phiof0}), and (\ref{EffectivePotentialUy}), one can get \begin{eqnarray}
  U(0)=\frac{\phi ''(0)}{2(\phi_0+1)}-\frac{3}{2} b k^2=\frac{3}{2} b k^2-\frac{3}{2} b k^2=0. \nonumber
\end{eqnarray}
Thus, the shape of the effective potential of the
gravitational fluctuation is always a double well for any positive parameters $b$ and $k$.
From the asymptotic behaviour of the warp factor $A(y\rightarrow \pm \infty) \rightarrow -bk|y|$ and scalar profile $\phi(y\rightarrow \pm \infty)\rightarrow c_1$,

it is easy to check that the corresponding graviton zero mode for model B can also be normalizable:
$\int H_0^2(z) dz<\infty$. Therefore, the graviton zero mode can be localized on the brane.



